orted the savings and consumption patterns of certain nations. Pettis examines the reasons behind these destabilizing policies, and he predicts severe economic dislocations that will have long-lasting effects.Demonstrating how economic policies can carry negative repercussions the world over, The Great Rebalancing sheds urgent light on our globally linked economic future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aBalance commerciale. 0aBalance of payments. 0aBalance of trade. 0aCapitaux étrangers. 0aCapitaux étrangers. 0aCommerce international. 0aCrise financière. 0aCrise financière. 0aDéséquilibres des paiements. 0aDéséquilibres des paiements. 0aFinancial crises. 0aFinanzkrise. 0aInternational economic relations. 0aInternational trade. 0aMacroéconomie. 0aMacroéconomie. 0aMondialisation. 0aRelations économiques internationales. 0aRelations économiques internationales. 0aWeltwirtschaftsordnung. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / International / Economics.2bisacsh1 aPettis, Michael.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311066592540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978140085226040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781400852260423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781400852260.jpg  a978-3-11-066592-5  Princeton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK